HEADWORD: Imbed
<hw>Im*bed"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Imbedded</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Imbedding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>im-</ets>
in + <ets>bed</ets>. Cf. <er>Embed</er>.]</ety> <def>To sink or lay, as
in a bed; to deposit in a partly inclosing mass, as of clay or mortar;
to cover, as with earth, sand, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

